== Mersey class ==

A recent edit suggested that the Mersey class is named for the lead ship in the class.  I haven't searched very thoroughly, but haven't found any evidence that such a ship existed.  These two sources suggest that there was no naval trawler called ''Mersey'':
:{{cite web |url=http://www.worldnavalships.com/naval_trawlers.htm |title=Naval Trawlers |website=Naval Ships of the Worlds Navies}}
:{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/warships/class.html?ID=335 |title=Mersey class |website=Uboat.net}}

So, the class-name format should rightly be: {{sclass2-|Mersey|naval trawler}}.

—[[User:Trappist the monk|Trappist the monk]] ([[User talk:Trappist the monk|talk]]) 11:46, 4 September 2013 (UTC)
